{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"taut-opera-ferry","description":"# Consolidate cross-session infra clones into shared helpers\n\n## What\n- One `run_git(cwd, *args, …)` replacing ~12 divergent `_git()` wrappers (raise vs None vs str returns).\n- One `atomic_write(path, data)` replacing ~25 inline temp+rename sites.\n- One `_lazy_load(key, filename)` for the 31 hand-rolled reconciler path-loaders (preserve the sys.modules key contract).\n- One `_reap_process_group(...)` shared by grounding + reconciler (currently byte-similar duplicates).\n- Converge NEW canonical-JSON hashing sites onto `_store/canonical.py` — but NOT the pinned attestation basis (attest.py/pass1.py), whose byte format is deliberately frozen.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Shared helpers land at the bottom of the dep stack (no new import cycles); call sites migrated.\n- [ ] The reconciler's stdlib-only isolation is preserved for its own copies where required.\n- [ ] Full suite green; commit(s) carry `rebar-ticket:` trailers.","id":"ba36-0b96-4d31-419b","parent_id":"9322-f84a-e047-4471","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Consolidate cross-session infra clones into shared helpers"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783056818019243001,"uuid":"0b2ce5b9-cc62-4ad2-97df-b781bc1eb8cb"}